               <msContents>
                  <summary>Nikandros and Peisikles had already written to Zenon to thank him for having arranged about the money due to them, and they now ask him to collect as much of it as he thinks convenient before Diotimos sails up.  They ask him also to dispose of the house and the vineyard as soon as possible, in order that they may suffer no loss from this source either.</summary>
